  "body": "PV controllers now use shared informers as of #41273\r\n\r\nThey default to a 15 second resync period, and depend on the resync to be responsive to PVC binding. Such a short resync period does not work well with other clients of the shared informers (like garbage collection), and depending on registration order, may not be honored (if the shared informer is already running, the PV binder's resync request is ignored).\r\n\r\nThe PV controller should use a work queue to requeue specific failed PV/PVC objects, rather than relying on a full resync of all objects to rekick specific failed objects.\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-storage-bugs \r\n@kubernetes/sig-scalability-bugs ",
